diff:1415955159:1415955146:=1c1%0a%3c [['''Generative e-book covers, by Casey Reas, 2014'''->http://www.nypl.org/blog/2014/09/03/generative-ebook-covers]]:Finding better covers for public domain ebooks.Book covers weren’t a big deal until the 20th century, but now they’re how people first interact with a book, so not having one really puts a book at a disadvantage. They are problematic, and not only in ebooks. It’s difficult to find high-quality, reusable covers of out-of-print or public domain books. There are some projects such as Recovering the Classics that approach this problem in interesting ways. However, we at NYPL are still left with very limited (and expensive) solutions to this problem.%0a---%0a> [['''Generative e-book covers, by Casey Reas'''->http://www.nypl.org/blog/2014/09/03/generative-ebook-covers]]:Finding better covers for public domain ebooks.Book covers weren’t a big deal until the 20th century, but now they’re how people first interact with a book, so not having one really puts a book at a disadvantage. They are problematic, and not only in ebooks. It’s difficult to find high-quality, reusable covers of out-of-print or public domain books. There are some projects such as Recovering the Classics that approach this problem in interesting ways. However, we at NYPL are still left with very limited (and expensive) solutions to this problem.%0a
